  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bb3\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baf \u0bb0\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b87\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc2.\u0b86\u0bb0\u0bcd. \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc0\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc2\u0bb2\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba8\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bcb\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0bb5\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0b9a\u0b95\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "From today, QR will be available nationwide. Supply of Fuel by Code - Ministry of Power",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "QR through National Fuel Permit Code-based fuel distribution will be rolled out across the country from today.",
        "According to the Ministry of Power and Energy, the ticket system and fuel distribution based on the final number of the vehicle number plate are void from today.",
        "In addition, the ministry has announced that ambulances can get required fuel at all fuel filling stations and has also provided a special phone number to provide information about those involved in illegal fuel hoarding, distribution and sale.",
        "A media release issued by the Ministry of Power and Energy further stated that:",
        "Accordingly, the procedures for dispensing fuel based on the final number of the vehicle number plate and through the registration token (token) are no longer valid.",
        "QR Fuel supply will be prioritized to fueling stations where the system is implemented. The fuel supplied in this manner will be supplied to the consumers only after verification through QR system.",
        "Those who face the problem of not being able to get the QR code using the vehicle registration numbers can get the QR code using their vehicle license plate number.",
        "All tricycles should be registered with their respective police stations and the tricycles so registered should recommend a fuel filling station near them.",
        "Accordingly, in the coming days, fuel will be distributed to the said tricycles only at their respective filling stations.",
        "The type of fuel required for fuel-driven machinery including generators, garden equipment, fuel requirement and selection of the fueling station expected to obtain it should be registered with the respective Divisional Secretariat.",
        "Businesses owning more than one vehicle can register all their vehicles with their Business Registration Number. Delivery of fuel to public transport vehicles has been prioritized.",
        "For such buses, fuel quota will be provided at the depots owned by the Sri Lanka Transport Board, based on which the amount of fuel that can be supplied will be determined based on the road permit and the distance traveled (kilometers). The said fuel can be obtained from the same depots or from a particular filling station.",
        "The fuel distribution for the vehicles involved in school services, office services, industry, tourism, ambulance vehicles and other essential service vehicles authorized by the authorities will be carried out at the depots owned by the Sri Lanka Transport Board.",
        "Ambulances will be given priority at all refueling stations and will be given the amount of fuel requested by their drivers. Steps have been taken to provide the quota reserved for the police department at selected fuel stations to each police station.",
        "Photos or videos of fuel filling stations or persons violating the regulations regarding illegal hoarding, sale or supply of fuel can be sent to WhatsApp number 074 212 3123.",
        "Repeatedly engaging in such illegal activities, QR The code will be invalidated and legal action will be initiated against them. Fuel can be obtained throughout the week at the fuel stations nationwide, up to the quota allocated for the respective vehicles. Therefore, the general public is requested not to cause inconvenience by waiting in queues unnecessarily near the filling stations."
      ],
